<glossentry id="split_infinitive">
    <glossterm>Split Infinitive</glossterm>
    <glossdef>
        <p>There is precedent from the fourteenth century downward for interposing an adverb between
                <i>to</i> and the infinitive which it governs, but the construction is in disfavor
            and is avoided by nearly all careful writers.</p>
